## Codex Tool Usage

- Pass an explicit `workdir` to shell command tools.
- Use `rtk` for token-heavy shell output: `rtk git status`, `rtk git diff`, `rtk rg`, `rtk pytest -q`, `rtk cargo test`.
- Use `rtk proxy` only when raw output is required.
- Use skills for occasional multi-step workflows so their detailed instructions load only when relevant.
- Delegate work only when the user and current runtime policy permit it. Keep approvals, public-contract decisions, integration, and final verification in the main agent.
